        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "test(agents): cover nonfatal trajectory flush timeout",
        "body": "Fixes #88520.\n\n## Summary\n\n- extract the embedded-attempt trajectory flush cleanup call into a small helper\n- add a regression test proving a stalled trajectory flush times out without rejecting attempt cleanup\n- keep the existing timeout logging and flush-state details intact\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior or issue addressed: The issue reported that a `pi-trajectory-flush` timeout could abort the agent run. Current `upstream/main` already uses the nonfatal cleanup timeout helper for `openclaw-trajectory-flush`; this patch locks that behavior at the embedded-attempt call boundary.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout at `/Users/andy/openclaw-88520`, branch `fix/trajectory-flush-nonfatal-88520`, commit `6c80fa8f95`.\n\nExact steps or command run after the patch:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/test-projects.mjs src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt-trajectory-flush-cleanup.test.ts src/agents/run-cleanup-timeout.test.ts\ngit log --format='%h %an <%ae> %s' upstream/main..HEAD\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: The cleanup helper and attempt-boundary regression tests passed, and the outgoing commit author was verified:\n\n```text\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\nTests  12 passed (12)\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 11.06s\n6c80fa8f95 Andy Ye <35905412+TurboTheTurtle@users.noreply.github.com> test: cover nonfatal trajectory flush timeout\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: A stalled trajectory recorder `flush()` resolves from the cleanup wrapper after the timeout, logs `agent cleanup timed out` with pending write details, and does not reject the attempt cleanup path.\n\nWhat was not tested: I did not reproduce the reporter's macOS I/O pressure event; the regression uses fake timers and a stalled flush promise to cover the reported failure mode deterministically.\n",
